And so when we delete SOX17, we also get a reduction in tumor burden, and then

1440
01:23:34.112 --> 01:23:37.052
also a reduction in some of these inflammatory mediators we think are driving the

1441
01:23:37.152 --> 01:23:37.452
myeloid

1442
01:23:38.352 --> 01:23:41.082
polarization and recruitment, such as IL6, CSF3, and

1443
01:23:41.152 --> 01:23:44.992
CCL2. So we think that this ALKB1 actually regulates LIF

1444
01:23:45.032 --> 01:23:48.152
expression, and then turn in this autocrine signaling loop express,

1445
01:23:48.732 --> 01:23:52.612
controls this whole dedifferentiation process, and this is SOX17 serves

1446
01:23:52.652 --> 01:23:56.492
as an intermediate to that process and that inflammation that occurs.

1447
01:23:58.232 --> 01:24:01.592
And then the final part I want to talk about is whether we can target LIF signaling

1448
01:24:01.632 --> 01:24:02.802
in a therapeutic manner.

1449
01:24:03.622 --> 01:24:06.962
And so currently, AstraZeneca has an antibody that's in clinical trials that's

1450
01:24:06.972 --> 01:24:08.852
being tested in non-small cell lung cancer.

1451
01:24:09.362 --> 01:24:13.112
And so we used an antibody that's adapted from that inner ALK1

1452
01:24:13.172 --> 01:24:15.392
tumor model, which has high expression of LIF.

1453
01:24:15.892 --> 01:24:18.832
We initiated our tumors, and then eight weeks after tumor

1454
01:24:18.872 --> 01:24:22.852
initiation, these tumors are already developing that dedifferentiation phenotype

1455
01:24:22.892 --> 01:24:26.452
and are infiltrated with these immunosuppressive myeloid populations.

1456
01:24:27.032 --> 01:24:30.632
We gave an anti-LIF antibody for three weeks and then measured the same outcomes

1457
01:24:30.652 --> 01:24:32.632
like tumor burden and immune infiltration.

1458
01:24:33.872 --> 01:24:37.492
We see that with the anti-LIF antibody, we get a reduction or

1459
01:24:37.592 --> 01:24:41.272
decrease in tumor burden at this endpoint, but we're also able to deplete those

1460
01:24:41.312 --> 01:24:45.132
immunosuppressive populations, the cyclic of high neutrophils and Arg1

1461
01:24:45.152 --> 01:24:46.392
interstitial macrophages.

1462
01:24:48.452 --> 01:24:51.692
Now, we also did single-cell analysis in that same experiment with the anti-LIF

1463
01:24:51.752 --> 01:24:55.532
antibody. And when we look at the ALK1 tumors seen here, we're able to

1464
01:24:55.592 --> 01:24:59.532
identify similar populations, including these SOX17 EMT-like

1465
01:24:59.572 --> 01:25:03.452
populations. These are circled here, and they lack NKX2.1,

1466
01:25:03.482 --> 01:25:07.452
have high expression of SOX17, and they also express markers of stemness, such

1467
01:25:07.492 --> 01:25:11.092
as KIT seen here. But this LIF antibody seems to be able to deplete these

1468
01:25:11.132 --> 01:25:14.732
populations. And so once again, they either depend on them for their maintenance

1469
01:25:14.772 --> 01:25:18.392
and they either die off or they actually become more of these well-differentiated

1470
01:25:18.472 --> 01:25:19.372
states seen here.

1471
01:25:21.432 --> 01:25:25.342
And so to summarize, these ALK bone immune tumors are quite distinct from

1472
01:25:25.412 --> 01:25:28.812
ALK bone wild-type tumors, which have minimal immunosuppressive myeloid

1473
01:25:28.832 --> 01:25:31.752
infiltration and to some extent, active T cell surveillance.

1474
01:25:32.502 --> 01:25:36.222
These ALK bone immune tumors, they have transcriptional reprogramming,

1475
01:25:36.292 --> 01:25:39.872
including autocrine LIF signaling, and this drives the tumor

1476
01:25:39.892 --> 01:25:43.452
plasticity and dedifferentiation process, as well as the inflammatory

1477
01:25:43.552 --> 01:25:47.532
program that reprograms or polarizes these myeloid populations that

1478
01:25:47.592 --> 01:25:51.292
subsequently lead to immune suppression and then dampened anti-tumor immunity.

1479
01:25:52.472 --> 01:25:56.432
But we can use an anti-LIF antibody to block this process and then also block

1480
01:25:56.492 --> 01:26:00.412
all these downstream processes to restore the anti-tumor immunity process.

1481
01:26:01.772 --> 01:26:04.552
And so this work, if you want to read more about it, it's also currently available

1482
01:26:04.652 --> 01:26:05.592
online as of today.

